[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pensioner detained over Crawley Asda store sex assault

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man convicted of sexually assaulting a four-year-old girl while she was sitting in a shopping trolley has been detained under the Mental Health Act.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Hugh Unwin, 75, of Garden Walk, Crawley, West Sussex, assaulted her in the town's Asda store last September.
At an earlier hearing, he was convicted of sexually assaulting a female under 13 and of breaching the conditions of the sexual offenders register.
At Lewes Crown Court, the judge made a Section 37 Hospital Order.
